Business Process for Your Business Listing System
1. Business Owner Registration & Onboarding
Business owners sign up and verify their accounts.

They choose a bundle (Free, Standard, Premium, etc.).

Allowed fields vary based on the selected bundle.

Payment is processed (if applicable).

Admin approves the listing (optional).

2. Business Listing Management
Business owners fill in details based on their bundle’s allowed fields (e.g., Name, Location, Services, Contact Info, Social Media, Images, Videos).

They can edit their listings based on the bundle’s flexibility (e.g., Premium allows frequent updates).

Listings expire after a set duration unless renewed.

3. Customer Interaction
Users (customers) search for businesses by category, location, or keywords.

They view business details (based on the bundle’s visibility settings).

Customers can contact businesses via chat, calls, or inquiries.

4. Analytics & Insights for Business Owners
Business owners can view analytics (e.g., profile views, inquiries, clicks).

Higher-tier bundles provide more detailed insights.

5. Payment & Subscription Management
Business owners can upgrade/downgrade bundles anytime.

Subscription renewal notifications are sent before expiry.

Payment processing through mobile money, credit cards, or PayPal.

6. Admin & Accountant Management
Admins manage users, businesses, and bundle settings.

Accountants handle financial records, revenue reports, and disputes.


Updated Functional Requirements
Business Management
✅ Business owners can register and manage their businesses.
✅ Businesses are linked to a region, district, ward, and street for location-based search.
✅ Business Registrars can register businesses and link them to owners.
✅ Each business has a verification and approval status (isVerified, isApproved).
✅ Listings expire if the bundle is not renewed (bundleExpiresAt).

Bundle & Subscription Management
✅ Businesses must select a bundle that determines allowed fields.
✅ Payment processing for premium bundles (paymentReference, paymentStatus).
✅ Businesses can view last payment date and bundle expiration (lastPaymentDate, bundleExpiresAt).

Search & Discovery
✅ Customers can search businesses by name, category, and location (region, district, ward, street).
✅ Map integration using latitude and longitude for nearby searches.

User Roles & Permissions
✅ Admins: Manage users, businesses, and bundle settings.
✅ Business Registrars: Register businesses and link them to business owners.
✅ Accountants: Handle financial records and payments.
✅ Business Owners: Manage their business listings.

Business Features
✅ Businesses can list their contact info (phone, email, website).
✅ Businesses can upload logo and cover image.
✅ Businesses can specify if they allow online booking and delivery (allowsOnlineBooking, allowsDelivery).
✅ Businesses have ratings and reviews (avgRating, numReviews).

Analytics & Insights
✅ Business owners can view profile views, clicks, and inquiries.
✅ Higher-tier bundles provide advanced analytics.

Updated Non-Functional Requirements
🔹 Scalability: The system should handle a growing number of users, businesses, and locations.
🔹 Performance: Fast loading times for search queries and business profiles.
🔹 Security: Secure authentication, data encryption, and payment protection.
🔹 Usability: Intuitive UI for both business owners and customers.
🔹 Availability: 24/7 uptime with minimal downtime.


